H0.text: Aqua Arnemetiae is the Roman name for which British town. Bath

H1.text: Aqua Arnemetiae is the Roman name for which British town. Harrogate

H2.text: Aqua Arnemetiae is the Roman name for which British town. Cheltenham

H3.text: Aqua Arnemetiae is the Roman name for which British town. Buxton

A4.text: Today it is the town of Buxton, Derbyshire in England.

A5.text: Aquae Arnemetiae and Aquae Sulis (modern town of Bath in Somerset) were the only two Roman bath towns in Britain.
